<h2>Vision</h2>
<p><span id="internal-source-marker_0.3925700980736011">Roots and tubers improving the lives of the poor</span></p>
<h2>Mission</h2>
<p><span id="internal-source-marker_0.3925700980736011">The  International Potato Center works with partners to achieve food  security, well-being, and gender equity for poor people in root and  tuber farming and food systems in the developing world. We do this  through research and innovation in science, technology, and capacity  strengthening.</span></p>
<h2><span>Core values</span></h2>
<p><b><span></span></b><span><b>Excellence: </b>We aim to excel in all we do.</span><span><b></b></span></p>
<p><span><b>Dignity and respect:</b> We treat each other and our partners with dignity and respect.</span><br /><span>Empowerment: We work to empower individuals at all levels for efficient, effective, and appropriate decision making.</span><span><b></b></span></p>
<p><span><b>Integrity:</b> We remain honest, transparent and accountable, individually and collectively, in what we say and do.</span><br /><span>Staff diversity: We are committed to staff diversity and aspire to provide an equal opportunity working environment.</span><span><b></b></span></p>
<p><span><b>Staff development:</b> We are committed to providing opportunities for professional and personal development.</span><br /><span>Innovation and creativity: We value innovation and creativity across our business.</span><span><b></b></span></p>
<p><span><b>Partnership:</b> We actively participate in and encourage dynamic partnerships.</span></p>